Ask HN: Is getting attention for startups harder in 2022?
text:
I founded my first startup back in 2011 and sold it in 2013. Back then it felt like not getting attention as a new startup was almost impossible, even without much marketing efforts.

Nowadays getting attention seems way harder in the constant growing sea of startups. Heck, it feels like there 1000x more startups than back in 2011. You can even think of the craziest ideas, only to find out later that there are already a few (if not dozens) of startups out there doing that very thing or at least in similar form.

Not saying it’s impossible or not worth pursuing, but damn did things got harder. Not?

Ask HN: Does TopTal Work as a Freelancer?
text:
I’m in the process of interviewing with TopTal and have passed the initial test however I’m getting some red flags with their process. The largest being they have a take home assignment which should take between 24 and 48 hours to complete! Oh and they don’t pay you your hourly rate to complete it either.

The only person I’ve been able to talk to was unable to tell me if my expected rate of USD$300/hr is realistic, all they said is you set your own rate.

So Ask HN, do you have experience freelancing with TopTal? What’s your hourly rate?

Edit: I’m Devops/SRE, but interested to hear from everyone
